A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 28, 2025, as Andrew J. Young Day at the state capitol; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Andrew J. Young has earned worldwide recognition as a pioneer and champion
4 of civil and human rights who has dedicated more than 65 years to public service through
5 roles in government, diplomacy, and advocacy; and
6 WHEREAS, through his leadership, countries throughout the world have created a successful
7 model that combines religion, education, democracy, and free enterprise in ways that support
8 the public good; and
9 WHEREAS, he began his political career in the United States House of Representatives as
10 the first African American representative from the State of Georgia since Reconstruction and
11 thereafter served as the United States ambassador to the United Nations under President
12 Jimmy Carter; and
13 WHEREAS, during his tenure as the United States ambassador, he negotiated an end to
14 white-minority rule in Namibia and Zimbabwe as well as promoted President Carter's
15 emphasis on human rights in global diplomacy efforts; and
