16 WHEREAS, as a two-term Mayor of Atlanta, Andrew J. Young was instrumental in the city's
17 economic expansion, attracting more than 1,100 businesses, securing over $70 billion in
18 foreign direct investments, and generating more than a million jobs; and
19 WHEREAS, he has further served on numerous boards, including the Martin Luther King
20 Center for Nonviolent Social Change, Morehouse College, the Andrew Young School of
21 Policy Studies at Georgia State University, and AmericasMart; and
22 WHEREAS, he has been recognized with numerous prestigious awards, including an Emmy
23 Lifetime Achievement Award in 2011 and the Dan Sweat Award in 2017, and his portrait has
24 been inducted into the permanent collection of the Smithsonian National Portrait Gallery,
25 cementing his legacy in American history; and
26 WHEREAS, the devotion of his time, efforts, and energy to the service of others and his
27 many achievements are worthy of recognition during this special time.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
29 recognize February 28, 2025, as Andrew J. Young Day at the state capitol in honor of his
30 extraordinary contributions to civil rights, diplomacy, public service, and economic
31 development.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
33 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Andrew J. Young.
